contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:06.857 --> 02:09.091
I've never tried that.

02:09.158 --> 02:10.292
[Knock on door]

02:10.360 --> 02:11.660
<i>Willa: Mom.</i>

02:11.729 --> 02:14.029
<i>There's a photographer downstairs.</i>

02:14.098 --> 02:16.264
<i>You need to take a shot for the papers.</i>

02:19.737 --> 02:20.969
Please.

02:21.038 --> 02:24.272
Open the door.

02:24.341 --> 02:27.175
The press already
thinks something's wrong.

02:32.649 --> 02:35.751
I'll take care of it,
okay? I'll get rid of him.

02:35.819 --> 02:38.186
We just need to get
through the next few months,

02:38.255 --> 02:40.722
and then it'll be like
he was never even here.

02:45.329 --> 02:48.263
I thought he'd be different.

02:48.332 --> 02:50.832
You thought he would be your brother?

02:53.604 --> 02:55.704
I'm sorry.

02:55.773 --> 02:59.241
Well, that makes it all better.

03:14.858 --> 03:17.459
Good morning.

03:17.528 --> 03:18.994
I still can't do it.

03:35.379 --> 03:36.678
Mom?

03:36.747 --> 03:37.879
Don't call me that again.

03:37.948 --> 03:39.414
What?

03:39.483 --> 03:41.450
I know what you did to my son.

03:44.054 --> 03:44.820
I...

03:44.888 --> 03:47.355
There.

03:47.424 --> 03:49.658
Windsor knot.

03:49.726 --> 03:51.693
[Indistinct conversations in distance]

03:57.701 --> 04:01.269
[Indistinct conversations echoing]

04:03.373 --> 04:04.840
Welcome to the circus.

04:10.681 --> 04:12.114
Can I get you to stand over here?

04:15.085 --> 04:16.284
[Camera shutter clicks]

04:23.794 --> 04:26.828
Acceptance speech is at 5:00 tonight.

04:26.897 --> 04:29.965
Woman: The photographer is
ready for you, Mrs. Warren.

04:33.137 --> 04:34.136
Mom?

04:34.204 --> 04:36.371
Why don't you sit down? Um...

04:43.347 --> 04:45.647
[Door closes]

04:49.066 --> 04:56.918
Synced and corrected by VitoSilans
- www.Addic7ed.com -

04:58.095 --> 05:00.195
Forensics got traces of
Scarlet Oak off the bastard's boot.

05:00.264 --> 05:01.563
It's a shot in the dark, I know,

05:01.632 --> 05:03.665
but it only grows in this
little pocket in the North Woods.

05:03.734 --> 05:04.833
There are cabins up there.

05:04.902 --> 05:06.268
If we could just get
a team on the ground.

05:06.336 --> 05:07.903
Clements: Hey, babe.

05:07.971 --> 05:09.504
I'm an idiot.

05:09.573 --> 05:10.872
Sorry I haven't called.

05:10.941 --> 05:14.876
I'm just gonna lay low till I even out.

05:14.945 --> 05:17.612
I love you.

05:17.681 --> 05:19.948
He called his husband last night.

05:20.017 --> 05:21.283
He's fine, Nina.

05:31.995 --> 05:36.364
Jane: Ravioli, corn, and
a few protein shakes.

05:36.433 --> 05:40.936
Um, I'll open it up so you
can get to it all real easy.

05:46.376 --> 05:48.710
Where's your monster taking you?

05:54.084 --> 05:57.385
Canada.

05:57.454 --> 05:58.687
Romantic.

05:58.755 --> 06:00.722
Once we're there, I'll call the police.

06:00.791 --> 06:02.824
I will let them know where to find you.

06:04.761 --> 06:06.761
I'll be nice and dead by then.

06:13.070 --> 06:14.970
I don't want to go with him.

06:15.038 --> 06:17.639
Then don't.

06:18.909 --> 06:21.476
I have a baby to protect.

06:21.545 --> 06:25.480
Kids become their parents, Jane.

06:30.621 --> 06:31.786
[Vehicle door opens]

06:35.125 --> 06:36.324
[Vehicle door closes]

06:37.194 --> 06:39.060
в™Є в™Є

07:27.577 --> 07:30.111
[Sighs]

07:50.367 --> 07:53.601
Adam: Hi, Mom.

08:08.452 --> 08:10.485
What took you so long?

08:12.487 --> 08:15.294
Honey. Oh.

08:15.362 --> 08:17.830
My sweet boy.

08:17.898 --> 08:19.164
Why are you crying?

08:19.233 --> 08:21.567
[Inhales sharply]

08:21.635 --> 08:23.068
Because you're not real.

08:23.137 --> 08:25.804
I'm just imagining you.

08:25.873 --> 08:27.473
Why does that make me not real?

08:27.541 --> 08:29.408
Oh, God.

08:29.477 --> 08:31.076
I miss you so much.

08:31.145 --> 08:33.345
I was right here.

08:33.414 --> 08:35.414
I didn't know.

08:35.482 --> 08:37.381
I didn't know.

08:41.856 --> 08:43.554
I'm... I'm here now.

08:43.624 --> 08:45.524
[Inhales sharply] Oh, God.

08:45.593 --> 08:46.925
Oh.

08:54.635 --> 08:58.237
We'll start over, dig another tunnel.

08:58.305 --> 09:01.039
We're bigger now.

09:01.108 --> 09:03.842
We'll dig faster.

09:03.911 --> 09:06.678
It won't take as long.

09:08.782 --> 09:10.282
Bear or Rabbit?

09:20.561 --> 09:22.127
We're gonna get out of here.

09:28.569 --> 09:30.269
You're right.

09:37.178 --> 09:38.977
But we're not going that way.

09:39.046 --> 09:41.113
Well, which way are we gonna go?

09:42.516 --> 09:45.117
There.

09:59.266 --> 10:00.699
Are you okay?

10:00.768 --> 10:02.968
I don't know what happened.

10:03.037 --> 10:05.837
Oh, your... your
scarf got caught in the wheel.

10:05.906 --> 10:07.472
My granny made that.

10:07.541 --> 10:09.007
Oh!

10:09.076 --> 10:10.409
It's Granny's fault, then.

10:10.477 --> 10:12.044
[Chuckles]

10:12.112 --> 10:14.112
Be careful.

10:17.151 --> 10:18.784
Could you give me a ride?

10:18.852 --> 10:21.820
I just live a few miles from here.

10:24.124 --> 10:25.791
Where's your mom?

10:25.859 --> 10:26.858
Work.

10:26.927 --> 10:29.561
But I'm not supposed to go this far.

10:29.630 --> 10:31.296
She'll be pissed.

10:33.334 --> 10:34.633
Oh.

10:34.702 --> 10:36.168
Well...

10:38.973 --> 10:42.507
we can't have that.

10:42.576 --> 10:43.709
What's your name?

10:43.777 --> 10:46.044
Devan.

10:46.113 --> 10:48.480
What's yours?

10:48.549 --> 10:50.649
Jim.

10:51.785 --> 10:53.285
What grade are you in, Devan?

10:53.354 --> 10:55.454
Sixth.

10:55.522 --> 10:57.189
That's a good one.

10:59.927 --> 11:02.661
Morning, sunshine.

11:02.730 --> 11:04.463
- Do you have a nervous stomach?
- No.

11:04.531 --> 11:06.331
Legal is shaking in their boots.

11:06.400 --> 11:07.332
His name is Ben Murphy.

11:07.401 --> 11:08.767
I've got his biological mother.

11:08.836 --> 11:10.369
I've got his birth
certificate. It's airtight.

11:10.437 --> 11:11.370
She's the governor now.

11:11.438 --> 11:12.371
Run it.

11:12.439 --> 11:13.839
Hell is gonna rain down.

11:13.907 --> 11:16.041
Run it.

11:18.579 --> 11:21.013
2,000 words and all your
research to back it up

11:21.081 --> 11:23.615
on my desk, 5:00 P.M.

11:23.684 --> 11:24.416
Above the fold?

11:24.485 --> 11:26.852
Above. Below.

11:26.920 --> 11:31.339
"Adam Warren is Ben
Murphy"... you got the whole front page.

11:32.324 --> 11:35.294
<i>Michelle: And how about
this political news out of Maine?</i>

11:35.362 --> 11:36.795
<i>Yeah, what's the story there?</i>

11:36.864 --> 11:39.264
<i>Soccer mom parks her
minivan at the governor's office?</i>

11:39.333 --> 11:40.232
<i>That's the story?</i>

11:40.301 --> 11:40.939
<i>Yeah. You know what?</i>

11:40.939 --> 11:43.266
<i>The woman's been through
hell with her family</i>

11:43.266 --> 11:45.337
<i>and instead of just,
like, awling under the covers</i>

11:45.406 --> 11:47.272
<i>like you and I would
do, she runs for offise.</i>

11:47.341 --> 11:48.370
<i>On what platform?</i>

11:48.371 --> 11:49.508
<i>You know what? I'd vote for her.</i>

11:49.576 --> 11:50.842
<i>Why? Based on her son?</i>

11:50.911 --> 11:52.244
<i>Yeah. Based on her son.</i>

11:52.313 --> 11:53.679
<i>You know, for 10 years, this poor kid...</i>

11:53.747 --> 11:55.247
<i>he was kept in some kind of a dungeon.</i>

11:55.316 --> 11:56.682
<i>I mean, what was it even? A hole?</i>

11:56.750 --> 11:57.938
<i>A... A pit.</i>

11:58.017 --> 12:00.619
<i>It was a dirty,
disgusting underground pit.</i>

12:00.688 --> 12:02.020
<i>[Echoing] Disgusting underground pit.</i>

12:02.089 --> 12:04.022
Happy to help.

12:07.661 --> 12:10.262
<i>Nina: Forensics got traces of
Scarlet Oak off the bastard's boot.</i>

12:10.331 --> 12:12.230
It only grows in this
little pocket in the North Woods.

12:12.299 --> 12:13.532
There are cabins up there.

12:13.600 --> 12:14.566
<i>[Echoing] Some kind of dungeon.</i>

12:14.635 --> 12:15.934
<i>Clements: Sorry I haven't called.</i>

12:16.003 --> 12:18.670
<i>I'm just gonna lay low till I even out.</i>

12:18.739 --> 12:19.705
<i>[Echoing] Some kind of dungeon.</i>

12:19.773 --> 12:21.807
<i>Some kind of a dungeon.</i>

12:29.783 --> 12:32.951
You all set?

12:33.020 --> 12:35.487
You put the car seat in?

12:35.556 --> 12:36.488
Yeah.

12:36.557 --> 12:37.689
You put it in right?

12:50.571 --> 12:51.670
Jane.

12:51.739 --> 12:53.438
What?

12:55.042 --> 12:57.376
Where's the shotgun?

12:57.444 --> 12:58.810
I don't know.

13:00.681 --> 13:02.080
Where is it, Jane?

13:04.084 --> 13:05.650
Why do you need it?

13:05.719 --> 13:07.085
[Sighs]

13:07.154 --> 13:08.220
You know why.

13:08.288 --> 13:10.088
You promised.

13:10.157 --> 13:11.823
You did this to him, not me.

13:14.495 --> 13:15.761
He has a family.

13:15.829 --> 13:17.295
So do you.

13:19.566 --> 13:20.966
[Sighs]

13:25.239 --> 13:27.205
It's outside in the trunk.

13:29.343 --> 13:31.410
[Sighs]

13:31.478 --> 13:34.279
в™Є в™Є

13:39.052 --> 13:42.988
[Door opens, closes]

13:44.324 --> 13:45.757
[Car alarm chirps]

13:45.826 --> 13:48.427
Detective Meyer, Red Pines PD.

13:48.495 --> 13:50.262
Well, you took a nice drive.

13:50.330 --> 13:51.696
Yeah.

13:51.765 --> 13:53.899
How many cabins like this
in the area, would you say?

13:53.967 --> 13:55.567
At least a dozen.

13:55.636 --> 13:57.969
Any of them have basements?

13:58.038 --> 14:00.539
Cellars or storage vaults?

14:00.607 --> 14:02.274
Why?

14:02.342 --> 14:05.043
The person I'm looking for
likes to keep things underground.

14:05.112 --> 14:07.479
Sorry. I don't know of any.

14:07.548 --> 14:09.414
Thanks anyways.

14:09.483 --> 14:11.082
[Gunshot]

14:11.151 --> 14:12.984
[Wings flapping]

14:18.225 --> 14:20.592
♪  ♪

15:12.710 --> 15:14.915
How did it happen?

15:16.285 --> 15:17.317
He had a dog.

15:19.488 --> 15:20.954
Oh.

15:21.023 --> 15:23.390
I wanted to give it a treat.

15:23.459 --> 15:25.392
He took me to his truck.

15:25.461 --> 15:30.397
How many times have I
told you never get in a car

15:30.466 --> 15:32.866
with someone that you don't know?

15:32.935 --> 15:34.101
But he had a dog.

15:34.170 --> 15:36.003
I don't care if he had an elephant.

15:36.071 --> 15:39.106
You never get in a stranger's car.

15:39.175 --> 15:41.208
Ever, ever. We have gone over this.

15:41.277 --> 15:42.843
Your father and I have gone over

15:42.912 --> 15:45.279
- and over and over this with you...
- Mom...

15:45.347 --> 15:46.507
since you were 5 years old.

15:46.515 --> 15:48.282
So what the hell were you thinking?

15:48.350 --> 15:50.551
You... you just...
you just went with him

15:50.619 --> 15:52.319
like... like a lamb to the slaughter,

15:52.388 --> 15:54.188
and you were smart!

15:54.256 --> 15:56.390
That is the worst
part. You were so smart.

15:56.459 --> 15:57.991
You were such a bright boy.

15:58.060 --> 16:02.529
How in this one moment
could you be so stupid?!

16:05.034 --> 16:06.366
I'm sorry. No.

16:06.435 --> 16:07.401
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

16:07.470 --> 16:09.136
I'm sorry.

16:09.205 --> 16:10.437
I love you.

16:13.943 --> 16:16.043
Doug: Bracelets.

16:21.016 --> 16:22.950
Adam: What'd you bring?

16:23.018 --> 16:24.151
Doughnuts.

16:24.220 --> 16:25.118
Yay.

16:30.926 --> 16:32.726
Ben hurt his hand.

16:32.795 --> 16:34.394
What happened?

16:34.463 --> 16:35.796
Rat bite.

16:35.865 --> 16:37.498
I told you we need traps.

16:37.566 --> 16:38.565
I was asking Ben.

16:43.939 --> 16:45.572
Looks okay to me.

16:45.641 --> 16:47.975
Under the shirt, it's all gross.

16:56.318 --> 16:58.448
Now! Get the key!

16:58.448 --> 16:59.686
- [Grunting, groaning]
- It's in his pocket.

16:59.755 --> 17:01.488
Just get his key!

17:01.557 --> 17:03.790
Ben, come on! Ben!

17:03.859 --> 17:04.790
Ben!

17:04.859 --> 17:06.760
Help me!

17:06.829 --> 17:07.994
Help me, Ben!

17:08.063 --> 17:09.128
[Groans]

17:09.198 --> 17:11.098
The key!

17:11.165 --> 17:12.566
Ben!

17:12.635 --> 17:14.434
[Groaning]

17:23.244 --> 17:25.045
[Breathing heavily]

17:33.022 --> 17:34.888
That?

17:34.957 --> 17:36.790
That isn't on me.

17:53.242 --> 17:54.541
Oh, my God.

17:56.579 --> 17:58.178
Hey, kid.

17:58.247 --> 18:01.114
You got my message.

18:01.183 --> 18:03.183
Did we get him?

18:03.252 --> 18:04.418
Jane shot him and left.

18:04.486 --> 18:06.153
So we got him.

18:06.221 --> 18:08.589
Not on the Warren kid.

18:08.657 --> 18:10.591
Why not?

18:10.659 --> 18:12.192
It doesn't matter. We got him on you.

18:12.261 --> 18:13.860
Hey, this is Detective Meyer.

18:13.929 --> 18:15.262
I need back-up, ambulances,

18:15.331 --> 18:17.464
North Woods eastern
edge by Lake Harriet.

18:17.533 --> 18:18.430
Meyer.

18:18.537 --> 18:20.601
Agent Clements needs medical attention
immediately, as well.

18:20.669 --> 18:23.337
Meyer, we don't have him.

18:23.405 --> 18:28.408
[Groans]

18:29.445 --> 18:31.845
What are you talking about?

18:31.914 --> 18:33.113
I can't ID him.

18:33.182 --> 18:35.215
I never saw him.

18:35.284 --> 18:37.551
What?

18:37.620 --> 18:38.919
He sent her.

18:38.988 --> 18:40.921
He always sent her.

18:50.099 --> 18:51.131
[Chips clacking]

18:55.104 --> 18:58.171
Bets, please. Place your bets.

18:58.240 --> 19:00.007
What are you playing?

19:00.075 --> 19:02.109
Texas Hold'em.

19:02.177 --> 19:03.577
What's that?

19:03.646 --> 19:05.912
[Chuckles]

19:05.981 --> 19:08.315
Poker.

19:08.384 --> 19:09.850
You want to play?

19:09.918 --> 19:12.386
Come on.

19:12.454 --> 19:15.656
All right. So, you get two cards.

19:15.724 --> 19:18.625
And you want to assume that
the other guy already has a pair,

19:18.694 --> 19:21.094
but we've only got an
ace high and a five.

19:21.163 --> 19:22.596
So, not a pair.

19:22.665 --> 19:25.866
You want to raise or stay?

19:25.934 --> 19:27.034
Raise.

19:30.105 --> 19:31.004
Ooh. All right.

19:31.073 --> 19:33.907
So now we got a pair of fives.

19:33.976 --> 19:36.810
So do we want to raise or stay?

19:36.879 --> 19:39.046
Raise.

19:39.114 --> 19:40.047
Ballsy.

19:40.115 --> 19:41.915
I like it.

19:41.984 --> 19:43.183
[Chips clacking]

19:44.019 --> 19:46.753
It wasn't your fault.

19:46.822 --> 19:48.188
What?

19:48.257 --> 19:51.925
It didn't matter that you
walked away from Willa that day.

19:51.994 --> 19:54.528
He knew who he wanted.

19:54.596 --> 19:56.697
He would have just
taken him another time.

20:01.303 --> 20:03.303
What... What are you...
What are you talking about?

20:03.338 --> 20:06.540
The guy who took him.

20:06.608 --> 20:07.874
What?

20:07.943 --> 20:10.077
And if I wasn't at an arcade that day,

20:10.145 --> 20:13.046
he would have just taken
me somewhere else, too.

20:13.115 --> 20:15.449
Dude, you weren't at the arcade.

20:15.517 --> 20:19.352
You were at the park.

20:19.421 --> 20:20.654
No.

20:21.990 --> 20:24.725
That was Adam.

20:24.793 --> 20:27.694
My name is Ben.

20:34.403 --> 20:36.269
<i>- [Bell chimes]
- We've got a winner.</i>

20:41.577 --> 20:42.609
Mom?

20:42.678 --> 20:44.111
Hmm?

20:44.179 --> 20:46.913
I have to go now.

20:46.982 --> 20:48.415
No.

20:48.484 --> 20:49.249
I have to.

20:49.318 --> 20:50.117
No.

20:50.185 --> 20:51.651
Please don't.

20:51.720 --> 20:52.986
I can't stay here forever.

20:53.055 --> 20:55.122
Just one more minute.

20:55.190 --> 20:56.656
- Mom.
- Just one more.

21:01.884 --> 21:07.522
♪ ♪

21:47.177 --> 21:49.044
I can't find my mother.

21:49.113 --> 21:49.878
What?

21:49.947 --> 21:51.146
She's gone.

21:51.215 --> 21:52.614
Where'd she go?

21:52.683 --> 21:55.083
Why do people say that when
you say you can't find something?

21:55.119 --> 21:56.451
I don't know. That's the point.

21:56.520 --> 21:58.186
What do you need? Why am I here?

21:58.255 --> 22:00.755
My story's running tomorrow.

22:00.824 --> 22:02.290
About?

22:02.359 --> 22:05.193
Your brother not being your brother?

22:05.262 --> 22:07.762
[Scoffs] How are we back here again?

22:07.831 --> 22:09.998
Because I found his mother.

22:17.808 --> 22:20.675
She works at a truck
stop. Her name is Sally.

22:23.080 --> 22:25.680
Did you tell her about Ben?

22:25.749 --> 22:28.083
Not yet.

22:31.421 --> 22:32.587
Do you want money?

22:34.525 --> 22:35.457
No.

22:37.961 --> 22:39.094
What do you want?

22:39.163 --> 22:41.229
[Sighs]

22:41.298 --> 22:42.664
A comment.

22:46.670 --> 22:48.203
This is absolute nonsense.

22:48.272 --> 22:51.740
This is tabloid journalism at its worst.

22:51.808 --> 22:54.342
And timed right after an election,

22:54.411 --> 22:57.078
it's clear the reporter's
goal is only to malign

22:57.147 --> 23:02.817
and further hurt a family already
in unspeakable pain.

23:02.886 --> 23:03.919
That's it?

23:03.987 --> 23:05.420
No, I'm not done.

23:05.489 --> 23:07.088
You'll get your 15 minutes.

23:07.157 --> 23:09.024
They'll do your hair and makeup

23:09.092 --> 23:11.226
for CNN and "Good Morning America"

23:11.295 --> 23:13.828
and they'll give you free bottled water,

23:13.897 --> 23:15.030
which you should load up,

23:15.098 --> 23:16.498
and for one week,

23:16.567 --> 23:20.669
they will make you feel very
special and very pretty.

23:22.339 --> 23:24.773
And then it'll be over because one story

23:24.841 --> 23:27.542
doesn't turn you into a
legitimate journalist.

23:27.611 --> 23:28.877
It doesn't build a career.

23:28.946 --> 23:31.680
One story makes you a
hot flash in a dirty pan.

23:36.587 --> 23:38.520
What's the offer, Willa?

23:41.391 --> 23:45.427
Unprecedented access to
the Governor's mansion.

23:45.495 --> 23:48.597
First dibs on anything and
everything, exclusives.

23:48.665 --> 23:51.433
You will be the boss of
us until the end of time.

23:53.136 --> 23:55.170
Why would you ever do that?

23:55.239 --> 23:56.738
What?

23:56.807 --> 23:59.374
Give up control when it's the
one thing that makes you happy?

23:59.443 --> 24:00.575
Desperate times.

24:00.644 --> 24:02.444
I'd own you.

24:05.148 --> 24:07.349
You already do.

24:07.417 --> 24:09.784
Thanks for this.

24:09.853 --> 24:13.021
[Door opens]

24:13.090 --> 24:14.289
[Door closes]

24:16.326 --> 24:17.225
Good boy.

24:17.294 --> 24:18.957
Come here, boy. Come on.

24:19.320 --> 24:20.662
- That's a good boy.
- [Ball squeaks]

24:20.731 --> 24:23.031
Davis: Nothing yet.

24:23.100 --> 24:25.033
How does a man keep a child underground

24:25.102 --> 24:27.269
and have nothing in his
house to show for it?

24:27.337 --> 24:29.204
He's a respectable homeowner.

24:29.273 --> 24:31.239
Give me kiddy porn or something.

24:31.308 --> 24:33.341
Plays a lot of "Candy Crush."

24:33.410 --> 24:35.143
[Dog whimpering]

24:44.288 --> 24:46.688
What's wrong, boy?

24:46.757 --> 24:48.156
Here, boy. Come on.

24:48.225 --> 24:49.424
Get the ball.

24:49.493 --> 24:51.026
- [Dog whimpering]
- Get the ball.

24:51.094 --> 24:52.527
Come on.

24:59.736 --> 25:02.003
There's an electric fence here.

25:02.072 --> 25:03.905
It shocks him if he crosses it.

25:03.974 --> 25:05.140
Davis: So?

25:05.208 --> 25:06.975
So it usually stops the
dog from getting out,

25:07.044 --> 25:08.677
not from getting in.

25:08.745 --> 25:10.445
What's he trying to protect there?

25:10.514 --> 25:13.415
Something he doesn't want dug up.

25:22.826 --> 25:23.986
Devan: Thanks for the slushie.

25:25.629 --> 25:27.295
You're welcome.

25:27.364 --> 25:31.333
Mom doesn't let me have it.

25:31.401 --> 25:32.967
You're not a diabetic, are you?

25:33.036 --> 25:36.271
[Chuckles]

25:36.340 --> 25:37.639
I like your car.

25:42.145 --> 25:43.845
I like your house.

25:43.914 --> 25:45.947
[Both chuckle]

26:06.970 --> 26:09.137
You should go on inside.

26:09.206 --> 26:10.271
What?

26:10.340 --> 26:11.573
Go on. Get out of the car.

26:13.310 --> 26:14.509
I-I can't.

26:14.578 --> 26:15.977
Just get out of the car.

26:16.046 --> 26:16.766
I can't!

26:16.767 --> 26:17.979
Get out of the car!

26:29.893 --> 26:32.560
[Breathes unsteadily]

26:54.317 --> 26:55.450
Hello.

26:55.519 --> 26:58.653
I canceled the rest of your day.

26:58.722 --> 27:00.522
If you're not planning

27:00.590 --> 27:04.125
on giving an acceptance
speech tomorrow...

27:04.194 --> 27:06.294
I'll give the speech.

27:08.398 --> 27:12.867
You look like a chimney sweep.

27:12.936 --> 27:14.235
I'll shower.

27:14.304 --> 27:16.704
Where have you been?

27:16.773 --> 27:21.509
I guess it's called an
oil tunnel or a bunker.

27:21.578 --> 27:22.677
I don't know.

27:22.746 --> 27:24.646
It's not a place that deserves a name.

27:24.714 --> 27:26.214
That's where you went?

27:26.283 --> 27:27.949
You should see it, too.

27:28.018 --> 27:29.584
Why?

27:29.653 --> 27:35.890
For 10 years, he was kept in
a dirty cage like an animal.

27:39.496 --> 27:42.464
It's not his fault if he became one.

27:47.204 --> 27:50.071
Okay.

27:50.140 --> 27:51.573
Okay.

27:53.944 --> 27:57.245
[Breathes deeply]

27:57.314 --> 27:58.880
- So where is he?
- [Sniffles]

28:08.592 --> 28:10.625
He's gone.

28:13.507 --> 28:16.340
[Knock on door]

28:22.214 --> 28:23.981
- They got your guy.
- What?

28:24.050 --> 28:25.382
The guy you told her about.

28:25.451 --> 28:26.617
Oh, g-good.

28:26.686 --> 28:30.321
Yeah. You were right, so...

28:30.389 --> 28:31.989
What are you doing here?

28:32.058 --> 28:36.226
Well, I thought we could throw
one back together to celebrate.

28:38.331 --> 28:39.630
Do you want a glass?

28:42.234 --> 28:45.002
I thought it'd feel different.

28:45.071 --> 28:46.136
What?

28:46.205 --> 28:48.906
Catching him.

28:48.974 --> 28:50.240
Cheers.

28:55.047 --> 28:56.513
[Sighs]

29:00.886 --> 29:03.220
So, what was he like?

29:06.492 --> 29:09.326
Long, pointy tail, carried a pitchfork.

29:10.996 --> 29:12.496
[Sighs]

29:12.565 --> 29:14.832
How do you take a
kid, an innocent child,

29:14.900 --> 29:17.501
his whole life ahead of him?

29:17.570 --> 29:19.803
What kind of a monster does that?

29:22.208 --> 29:24.041
You're asking me, John?

29:24.110 --> 29:27.144
No. No.

29:39.992 --> 29:42.092
Yeah.

29:52.638 --> 29:56.673
It's just...

29:56.742 --> 29:58.108
desire.

29:59.812 --> 30:02.413
That you know you shouldn't have.

30:02.481 --> 30:05.616
But you want it anyway.

30:05.684 --> 30:07.451
Chocolate.

30:07.520 --> 30:08.786
Whiskey.

30:08.854 --> 30:13.290
Yeah, but taking a kid is not
like eating a Hershey bar.

30:13.359 --> 30:15.325
You've never had an urge?

30:15.394 --> 30:17.361
Not like that, no.

30:19.198 --> 30:20.164
What about her?

30:20.232 --> 30:22.099
- What?
- The detective.

30:22.168 --> 30:24.001
You shouldn't have done
that, but you did it.

30:24.069 --> 30:25.769
Are you trying to compare me to...

30:25.838 --> 30:28.472
I'm just talking about
wanting what we shouldn't want.

30:28.541 --> 30:30.007
- Well, that's different.
- Why?

30:30.075 --> 30:32.509
She's a consenting adult.

30:32.578 --> 30:34.077
Okay.

30:36.215 --> 30:37.975
Have you ever wanted to
have sex with a woman

30:38.017 --> 30:39.383
that didn't want to have sex with you?

30:39.452 --> 30:40.284
That's rape.

30:40.352 --> 30:41.185
Yes.

30:41.253 --> 30:42.219
- That's wrong.
- Yes.

30:42.288 --> 30:43.120
I'd never do it.

30:43.189 --> 30:44.354
Neither would I.

30:47.226 --> 30:49.560
Wanting it doesn't make you the monster.

30:49.628 --> 30:51.495
Taking it does.

31:00.005 --> 31:01.638
[Elevator bell dings]

31:03.676 --> 31:04.983
Hey.

31:07.046 --> 31:08.445
- Is the story on my desk?
- Mm-hmm.

31:08.514 --> 31:09.813
All the research, too, right?

31:09.882 --> 31:11.215
Everything I got.

31:13.118 --> 31:14.627
Good.

31:16.822 --> 31:18.288
- Gus.
- Yeah.

31:18.357 --> 31:21.391
You should have given
me a byline sooner.

31:21.460 --> 31:22.860
[Elevator bell dings]

31:42.648 --> 31:43.580
Mom.

31:46.785 --> 31:48.919
Claire: Oh.

31:56.495 --> 31:58.662
What are you doing?!

31:58.731 --> 32:00.597
Trying to hitch a ride.

32:00.666 --> 32:02.733
Do you know how dangerous that is?

32:04.336 --> 32:05.435
Yeah.

32:13.212 --> 32:14.845
Come home.

32:17.483 --> 32:18.982
Okay.

32:24.490 --> 32:26.023
Wait.

32:26.091 --> 32:28.025
What?

32:28.093 --> 32:30.060
I did something.

32:31.964 --> 32:33.297
[Indistinct conversations]

32:41.273 --> 32:42.372
Two more, please.

32:53.852 --> 32:54.885
Um, again.

32:54.954 --> 32:58.288
This time, something
that takes mixing.

33:01.660 --> 33:03.961
You were right.

33:07.866 --> 33:09.066
I was going to tell you.

33:14.173 --> 33:15.172
No, I wasn't.

33:20.713 --> 33:25.048
It brought you back home. There's that.

33:30.255 --> 33:32.456
Can you just give me a rope burn?

33:34.827 --> 33:37.227
When I broke your Optimus Prime,

33:37.296 --> 33:40.697
you gave me one that was red for days.

33:42.368 --> 33:44.468
You said, "Close your
eyes and roll up your sleeve."

33:44.536 --> 33:47.237
And... And I was so dumb

33:47.306 --> 33:49.506
I thought you were gonna give
me a sticker or something.

33:52.544 --> 33:54.745
But at least it made it okay again.

34:01.353 --> 34:03.053
I love you.

34:08.994 --> 34:11.428
Close your eyes.

34:38.157 --> 34:40.023
Nina: Sorry to call you in so late.

34:41.893 --> 34:44.795
I have to give an
acceptance speech in the morning.

34:44.862 --> 34:48.965
I think I found your son.

34:49.034 --> 34:51.268
I... I'm sorry.

34:51.335 --> 34:54.404
We found human remains in
the suspect's backyard.

34:54.473 --> 34:57.107
All Forensics has got is that
it's an adolescent male.

34:59.945 --> 35:03.013
I'm gonna put him in a hole, Claire.

35:03.082 --> 35:05.015
For what he did to both of them.

35:05.084 --> 35:08.151
He should rot in a cage

35:08.220 --> 35:11.421
smaller than the one he locked them in.

35:11.490 --> 35:12.789
That's what he deserves,

35:12.858 --> 35:15.826
and I'm asking you to help me do it.

35:18.797 --> 35:20.831
What do you need?

35:20.899 --> 35:23.400
Your DNA to confirm it's Adam.

35:23.469 --> 35:24.534
[Sighs]

35:24.603 --> 35:26.503
It's the only way that you can get him?

35:26.572 --> 35:27.738
It's all I have left.

35:27.806 --> 35:29.072
- This will go public.
- Yes.

35:29.141 --> 35:30.807
I just won an election.

35:30.876 --> 35:31.641
Yes.

35:38.016 --> 35:42.385
Is there enough of my son left to bury?

35:42.454 --> 35:43.754
Yes.

35:56.535 --> 35:58.101
Do it.

36:02.598 --> 36:04.319
You ready?

36:04.388 --> 36:06.421
I just ran for Governor, right?

36:06.490 --> 36:09.391
And governors run for President.

36:09.459 --> 36:12.661
[Camera shutters
clicking, indistinct shouting]

36:29.079 --> 36:30.679
Good morning.

36:32.549 --> 36:36.351
I would like to thank
you all for coming,

36:36.420 --> 36:38.320
um...

36:38.388 --> 36:41.456
Governor Lang for his
gracious words last night,

36:41.525 --> 36:46.227
and all the voters who
came out on a very cold day

36:46.296 --> 36:50.432
and participated in
the political process.

36:50.500 --> 36:52.500
Um...

36:52.569 --> 36:59.174
I would not be here
without the support of my family.

36:59.242 --> 37:02.711
And it is for them that
I want to make our state

37:02.779 --> 37:07.182
a better place, a safer place.

37:10.354 --> 37:14.789
Because we all have the right

37:14.858 --> 37:18.693
to feel secure in our own neighborhoods.

37:18.762 --> 37:21.896
We deserve a world in which we can

37:21.965 --> 37:25.967
send our children off to
the bus stop in the morning

37:26.036 --> 37:29.971
without having to
worry they won't come back.

37:30.040 --> 37:34.376
That is my commitment
to the people of Maine.

37:34.444 --> 37:38.680
Here today, I will
make that world a reality.

37:43.620 --> 37:48.490
But great change doesn't
come without great sacrifice,

37:48.558 --> 37:52.060
and believe me,

37:52.129 --> 37:55.296
we know that better than anyone.

37:56.633 --> 37:58.566
The next four years won't be easy.

37:58.635 --> 38:00.034
Nothing important ever is,

38:00.103 --> 38:04.739
but I am ready to roll up my sleeves

38:04.808 --> 38:07.475
and do whatever it
takes for the brighter future

38:07.544 --> 38:09.778
that we all deserve.

38:09.846 --> 38:12.180
No matter what stands in my way,

38:12.249 --> 38:15.750
I will never stop fighting for you,

38:15.819 --> 38:19.220
for your families, and
for your children.

38:19.289 --> 38:22.957
I am so honored to be the next Governor

38:23.026 --> 38:25.894
of the great state of Maine.

38:27.197 --> 38:29.697
[Applause]

38:33.437 --> 38:34.936
[Sighs]

38:38.375 --> 38:39.541
It's not him.

38:39.609 --> 38:40.875
What?

38:40.944 --> 38:42.343
Forensics came back on the bones.

38:42.412 --> 38:43.545
It's some other kid.

38:43.613 --> 38:46.981
He was killed before
Warren was even taken.

38:49.386 --> 38:51.986
Then what happened to Adam?

38:53.490 --> 38:55.690
[Baby crying]

39:01.998 --> 39:05.233
[Crying continues]

39:08.305 --> 39:10.939
Is there a bottle back there?

39:14.611 --> 39:18.613
[Crying continues]

39:18.682 --> 39:20.415
I'm gonna run inside.

39:44.574 --> 39:46.441
Man: Help you with something?

39:46.510 --> 39:48.610
Do you have a phone?

39:48.678 --> 39:51.112
Over there.

39:53.617 --> 39:57.252
<i>Ben: Picture your life.</i>

39:57.320 --> 39:59.354
<i>I've lived two of them.</i>

39:59.422 --> 40:00.889
Did you even try it?

40:00.957 --> 40:02.924
The Governor-Elect doesn't
have time to taste all the food.

40:02.993 --> 40:06.661
Well, she should, because
it came from the pet aisle.

40:06.730 --> 40:09.197
[Laughter, telephone rings]

40:09.266 --> 40:11.699
<i>Every moment precious.</i>

40:11.768 --> 40:12.901
Claire: Someone get that?

40:14.437 --> 40:16.237
It's the press.

40:16.306 --> 40:19.173
Lang's concession speech isn't bad.

40:19.242 --> 40:21.709
Come on. My hands are wet.

40:21.778 --> 40:23.611
Let the machine get it.

40:23.680 --> 40:25.980
Oh, now it's bad. Listen to this.

40:26.049 --> 40:30.552
He says, "It has been an
honor serving the people of Maine,

40:30.620 --> 40:34.289
and I look forward to doing
it again in the future."

40:34.357 --> 40:35.723
It's just so blatant.

40:35.792 --> 40:37.225
I didn't think he'd
be this disrespectful.

40:37.294 --> 40:38.626
Hello?

40:44.000 --> 40:47.602
[Pounding]

40:58.114 --> 40:59.447
We have to go right now.

41:02.052 --> 41:04.118
There's something I need to do first.

41:12.062 --> 41:15.964
You took my life.

41:16.032 --> 41:17.722
I'm coming to get it back.

